one day on Disgrace and Tolmachevsky lake to make, \r\nAnd the price will a little change.\r\n ',1,'2010-07-19 17:45:07','2010-07-19 17:45:07'),(15,'Dry fly salmon fishing ','   Some experiments seem deprived of practical sense, simply absurd. I about catching of a salmon by small dry flies. If it was a question about bombers and provokers similar to them then it would be not necessary to mention it. Interest of a salmon to objects on a surface - history old and peculiar not only to the rivers of the north Kola. The same curiosity is shown by a salmon everywhere to the most different subjects dragged at a surface. Bomber it is only known in flyfishing a variant of a superficial bait. On a surface catch and metal lures.  \r\n\r\n<p align=center>\r\n<img src=\"../../images/events/dry_fly_fishing.jpg\" />\r\n</p>\r\nRead more in <a href=http://blog.chavanga.com/2010/07/dry-fly-salmon-fishing.html>Chavanga blog</a>.',1,'2010-07-23 10:45:45','2010-07-31 15:25:46'),(16,' Nymph salmon fishing ',' In most cases, we catch a salmon equally, a method of a classical wet fly, we throw downwards and across, selecting further speed, a direction and depth. \r\n\r\nThe method of a wet fly in all variants is productive enough. \"The salmon\" fly in usual, habitual execution, was created just for such technics. But…\r\n\r\n<p align=center>\r\n<img src=\"../../images/events/nymph_salmon_fishing.jpg\" />\r\n</p>\r\nRead more at <a href=http://blog.chavanga.com/2010/07/nymph-salmon-fishing.html>Chavanga blog</a>.',1,'2010-07-23 10:47:31','2010-07-31 15:23:57'),(17,'Arctic char paradise','After several years of exploring Greenland’s rivers we’ve managed to locate literary the most prolific fisheries on that harsh island and the most efficient means for reaching them. Our fishing grounds are quite away from civilization and can be reached either by sea or air. \r\n\r\n<p align=center>\r\n<img src=\"../../images/events/arctic_char_paradise/3.jpg\" width=600 /><br/>\r\n<img src=\"../../images/events/arctic_char_paradise/5.jpg\" width=600  /><br/>\r\n<img src=\"../../images/events/arctic_char_paradise/7.jpg\" width=600  /><br/>\r\n</p>\r\n<big>\r\nSee more photos at <a href=http://blog.chavanga.com/2010/07/arctic-char-paradise.html>Chavanga blog</a>.</big>',1,'2010-07-27 10:33:51','2010-07-31 15:22:21'),(18,'Kola autumn- NEW article on  www.globalflyfisher.com','Kola autumn - Horses, bears and fly-fishing \r\n\r\nWith the fly rod in the Kola Peninsula\r\n\r\nBy Mindaugas Banelisn \r\n\r\nSeptember, while sizzling my lard on the Turkish beach and sipping Efes Pilsen, I was thinking about the fact that I had already fulfilled one of the annual duties of a father and husband - having had a family holiday “in the South”.\r\nSo it was high time to take care of the truly manly rest, which is fishing somewhere in the North. The target was salmon. I had decided that Kola Peninsula was the ideal place to travel to. So I set off. It was not the first time I was traveling to Kola, but it was the first time in the autumn.\r\n\r\nMore.... in <a href=http://blog.chavanga.com/2010/07/with-fly-rod-in-kola-peninsula.html>Chavanga Blog</a>\r\n<p align=center><img src=\"../../images/events/global_flyfisher.png\"  /></p>',1,'2010-07-27 11:19:23','2010-07-31 15:13:12'),(19,'Pikes in a  salmon rivers.','The pike always was considered as undesirable fish there where there is a salmon or a trout. But in the nature they adjoined always. And if fishing pressure does not change this balance no trouble in the presence of a pike and is not present for the salmon. \r\n\r\nPlease, read more in Chavanga Blog, you can see it below Partners...',1,'2010-08-25 11:56:45','2010-08-25 11:56:45'),(20,' Less  water -   more fishes.','The hot summer was observed not only in Europe, but also on Kola Peninsula. A heat and absence of rains have led to falling of a water level and its warming up to 23 degrees. It was possible to expect sharp decrease in activity of fish. But it has not occurred....\r\n\r\n<a href=\'http://blog.chavanga.com/2010/08/there-is-less-than-water-more-fishes.html\'>Please, read more in Chavanga Blog</a>\r\n\r\n<p align=center>\r\n<img src=\'http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_1bVgby4N7Wk/THUHqXoQ9xI/AAAAAAAAAQ4/MLJbHLVpaok/s400/2.jpg\'/>\r\n</p>',1,'2010-08-25 11:58:41','2010-09-03 15:07:21'),(21,'Hungry diet or over effective digestion?','The low water level in the end of July and in the beginning of August has led to appreciable reduction of places of parking for Chavanga`sgraylings. Many reaches and wide floods of the river, pre threshold sites have lost water.  Probably, the forage lack has led to sharp increase of aggression of fish. \r\n\r\n<a href=\'http://blog.chavanga.com/2010/08/hungry-diet-or-over-effective-digestion.html\'>Read more...</a>\r\n\r\n<p align=center>\r\n<img src=\'http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_1bVgby4N7Wk/THULoVWKiPI/AAAAAAAAASw/XfKIlXQlKkI/s400/5.jpg\'/>\r\n</p>',1,'2010-08-25 12:01:32','2010-09-03 15:06:24'),(22,'Another way to fish salmon !!!',' Last   of 10 years me are carried away by catching of a salmon on flies which usually do not carry to the salmon. First of all   flies of the small sizes, in the second it often imitating flies, wet flies, nymphs. In the third, catching   to these flies is interesting to me by methods.    Last years  I collect a material on catching of a salmon on dry imitations of mayflies  and sedges. If you have an information on this theme - please, share it. Completely illustrated article\r\n\r\n\"Different view on catching of a salmon\"\r\n<a href=\'http://blog.chavanga.com/2010/08/different-view-on-catching-of-salmon.html\'>Part 1</a>\r\n<a href=\'http://blog.chavanga.com/2010/08/different-view-on-catching-of-salmon_28.html\'>Part 2</a>\r\n<a href=\'http://blog.chavanga.com/2010/08/different-view-on-catching-of-salmon_9081.html\'>Part 3</a>\r\n<a href=\'http://blog.chavanga.com/2010/08/different-view-on-catching-of-salmon_8587.html\'>Part 4</a>\r\n\r\nAbout theoretical preconditions of catching on not salmon flies it is possible to read more low in Chavanga Blog.\r\n<p align=center>\r\n<img src=\'http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_1bVgby4N7Wk/THj0A5vSG6I/AAAAAAAAAT4/yz3Qz76je20/s400/4.jpg\' />\r\n</p>',1,'2010-08-28 11:29:24','2010-09-03 15:05:11'),(23,'Latest News from Chavanga. Salmon activity.','Rather long hot summer with extremely low water level has led to the early beginning of spawning of a salmon. Already to the middle of September activity of resident fish has sharply fallen, began to come across already empty fishes.\r\n\r\nMore..... in Chavanga Blog below.',1,'2010-10-06 14:52:35','2010-10-06 14:52:35'),(24,'Kamchatka- full of fishes!!!','The first impressions after 10 day rounds are that - here full waters, is full some fish and it is possible to lose the way. The rivers even located near to dirt roads are so inaccessible that advancement is possible only by boats.\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n<img src=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_1bVgby4N7Wk/TKx7engEpNI/AAAAAAAAAVM/yRpyhpPRZ2o/s320/5.jpg\" />\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n Please, more in <a href=\"http://blog.chavanga.com/2010/10/kamchatka-full-of-rivers-waters-and.html\">Chavanga Blog</a>',1,'2010-10-06 14:55:37','2010-10-09 11:40:37'),(25,'Kamchatka BIG GAME. First part of our program. River Big fishing.','There was an impression that here it is a lot of fish, as from one place it was possible to catch 3-5 pieces, after an hour 2-3 more silver big fishes came across on a hook, and the others did not stop to lap at a surface. From a motor boat it was visible that the river really big, in it set of islands and branches with shelters for fishes. It is possible to tell that it is variant Big Game for Kamchatka. Two days have seemed too small term to understand and master all variants of catching. \r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n<img src=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_1bVgby4N7Wk/TK4PPavnTeI/AAAAAAAAAWc/RwNPGUcroP0/s320/1.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n Read more \r\n<a href=\"http://blog.chavanga.com/2010/10/kamchatka-catching-of-salmon-on-river.html\">http://blog.chavanga.com/2010/10/kamchatka-catching-of-salmon-on-river.html</a>',1,'2010-10-07 19:03:04','2010-10-09 11:39:03'),(26,'New territory. Chavanga top part adventure.','This site of the river is located above falls and is almost unknown to fishers. Under the preliminary information, the falls are high and impassable for a salmon, therefore this top part of the river is isolated. Here meet coregonus, a pike, a perch, fish usual for 2 lakes located here - Chavangsky and Zhilin\'s lake. But it was not believed that here, hardly above falls and already absolutely there is no salmon and a trout, grayling. \r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n<img src=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_1bVgby4N7Wk/TKyBrR93xdI/AAAAAAAAAWE/PvG6GztFDdE/s320/5.jpg\" />\r\n</p>\r\nMore in Chavanga jumping Blog in this left columne. Thank.',1,'2010-10-07 19:07:25','2010-10-09 11:37:37'),(27,'All NEWS about Chavanga tours! Don\'t forget to read our blog!','<p align=center>\r\n<img src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_1bVgby4N7Wk/TK4XkJ1DU5I/AAAAAAAAAY0/rDVcY7_-Z54/s320/11.jpg\" />\r\n</p>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.chavanga.com/2010_04_01_archive.html\">April Archive: How to get to Russia?</a><br/>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.chavanga.com/2010_05_01_archive.html\">May Archive: Foreign Posts</a><br/>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.chavanga.com/2010_07_01_archive.html\">July Archive: A lot of different posts; Where is the biggest one?, Arctic char paradise, Big fly – big trout, Chavanga`s huge grayling...</a><br/>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.chavanga.com/2010_08_01_archive.html\">August Archive: Different view on catching of a salmon</a><br/>\r\n\r\nAll info by Chavanga Blog in jumping window at left menu. \r\n<p align=center>\r\nJust Find that Image: <br/>\r\n<img src=\"http://chavanga.com/images/left_menu/blog_chavanga_logo.gif\" /></p>',1,'2010-10-07 19:13:09','2010-10-09 11:36:07'),(28,'Read about us at Wedkarstwo magazines.','Do you like to get more information about our tours?\r\nJust read fishing related magazines!\r\n<p align=center>\r\n<img src=\"http://chavanga.com/images/press/Wedkarstwo39/cover_small.jpg\" width=300/>\r\n<a href=\"http://chavanga.com/press/wedkarstwo39\">Wedkarstwo 39</a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=center>\r\n<img src=\"http://chavanga.com/images/press/Wedkarstwo56/cover_small.jpg\" width=300/>\r\n<a href=\"http://chavanga.com/press/wedkarstwo56\">Wedkarstwo 56</a>\r\n</p>\r\n',1,'2010-10-11 14:49:30','2010-10-11 14:49:55'),(29,'Kamchatka. Second part.River  Fast  fishing','Second part of our Kamchatka fishing trip. Not so far, but very interesting fishing program. Big river system, a lot of beautyfull places, verious fishes, all variants and methods of flyfishing + spinning, if you want.\r\nThis is an excellent opportunity to get a great fishing  in a low price.\r\nSee more, please, in Chavanga Blog below(jumping window).',1,'2010-10-18 11:47:18','2010-10-18 11:47:18'),(30,'Ouickly and angrily. Kamchatka once again. Plotnikova river.','Quickly - because the interesting site of the river can be passed for 1-2 days. The river is located absolutely near to our hotel and it is possible to reach water hour. The top site in the alloy beginning too represents an interlacing of sleeves of the river, big and fast, suddenly absolutely narrow and small. The river shares on some parts and set of its sleeves remain uninspected. Behind stones come across quite good chars and mikiza -   Kamchatka kind of rainbow trout. In places deeper and quiet on I will flash came across Silver salmons  in the spawning dress. Here too everywhere traces of summer abundance, remains of salmons, the bear tracks on coast. \r\nMore...in Chavanga Blog below - jumping   Chavanga.',1,'2010-10-18 14:47:16','2010-10-18 14:47:16'),(31,'The huge number of fresh fish has risen in the rivers of the White sea! ','The huge number of fresh fish has risen in the rivers of the White sea!\r\n\r\nThe latest news from the Chavanga river.\r\n\r\nThe most intensive has begun with the end of September during the last years calling of a salmon from the sea in the river. The set of fresh fish has risen from the sea. Such quantity it was not observed within several years. \r\n\r\nRead more in Chavanga Blog. Jumping window in a left columne. Thanks!',1,'2010-10-20 09:56:46','2010-10-20 09:56:46'),(32,'How to catch grayling? Here there is a help!','How to catch grayling? Here there is a help!\r\n Chavanga River has the big population of this fish. Many fishers consider as one of important advantages of the river that it is possible to catch not only a salmon, but also graylings. The problem is that northern summer is very short also a river condition changes very quickly. The behaviour  of graylings, their places of feeding and a forage changes also. Therefore we should search for each time a new suitable method of catching, and it happens hardly. Here, on a blog \"Chavanga\"  you will find a series of small articles with the review of a diet of this fish, the recommendation for choice places of catching and a catching method.\r\n\r\nClick the jumping window Chavanga below!',1,'2010-10-29 07:15:02','2010-10-29 07:15:02'),(33,'Grayling diet. We need to knew! View  #1 and #2','The greatest difficulty is  the cases of a selective  feeding of graylings. During such periods it don`t react on ordinary flies. If it is possible to find out character of its food then it is possible to find parking lots of fish and to pick up good fly. \r\nPlease, look in to the Chavanga Blog below.',1,'2010-10-29 09:43:29','2010-10-29 09:43:29'),(34,'Nothing to eat! Low water diet #3.','Stomachs of the studied fishes contained very   small amount of forage.    Here the rests of small insects and worm Gordius aquaticus are visible.  Usual  bottom fauna is  absent. In such conditions fish was active and reacted to bait immediately.\r\n\r\nPhotos and text in Chavanga Blog below. Thanks.',1,'2010-10-30 12:04:45','2010-10-30 12:04:45'),(35,'Biggest trouts!!!! North Kola program #6','We managed to organize fishing of these largest trouts on Kola Peninsula. It undoubtedly one of the best places for catching! Varzina Top camp.\r\nMore in Blog Chavanga, thanks!',1,'2010-11-03 14:32:13','2010-11-03 14:32:13'),(36,'New Photos At Gallery. Kamchatka River gallery.','See new photos at <a href=\'http://chavanga.com/image_gallery_groups/14\'>Kamchatka River gallery</a>.\r\n\r\n<a href=\'http://chavanga.com/image_gallery_groups/63\'> Big river ( images: 9 )</a>\r\n<a href=\'http://chavanga.com/image_gallery_groups/64\'>Karymchina river ( images: 8 )</a>\r\n<a href=\'http://chavanga.com/image_gallery_groups/65\'>Our hotel ( images: 9 )</a>\r\n<a href=\'http://chavanga.com/image_gallery_groups/66\'>Plotnikova river ( images: 11 ) </a>\r\n<a href=\'http://chavanga.com/image_gallery_groups/67\'>River Bystraja ( images: 17 )</a>',1,'2010-11-09 18:47:58','2010-11-09 18:48:08'),(37,'Very short news!','Very short news! But good news from Chavanga river! Good weather, good water level and a lot of good fishes in the river! We are waiting spring 2011 to open a new season!',1,'2010-11-22 20:25:07','2010-11-22 20:25:23'),(38,' 10 years! You can find yourself on Chavanga river!!   ','We start new photo gallery with you and your fish! From 2001 till 2010 year! 10 years we fish together on Chavanga river. All Europe, Island, Canada, USSR countries fish this famous part of the salmon world! Find yourself, may be you forgot this nice moment of your life. \r\n \r\nIn Blog Chavanga we put photo of our friends from 2001 year.\r\nThanks. ',1,'2010-11-26 15:43:25','2010-11-26 15:43:25'),(40,'common info ---  how to get to the Russia? ','Here is a common info about first problems of all our guests, \r\n                   how to get to the Russia? \r\n\r\nYour visa support.\r\n\r\n  After receiving your booking form correctly completed and signed we \r\nwill send the special Russian invitation that is needed to get the visa. We will mail \r\nyou the invitation form and this form has to be filled out and returned to us.\r\n\r\nEveryone traveling to Russia is responsible for obtaining his or her own visa.\r\nPlease notice that regulations require that you can only do so within three months \r\nof the start.  \r\n\r\nTo process your visa application it must to be sent to a consulate or local \r\nvisa agent and contact one of the specialist travel company in your country\r\n that deal with this.\r\n\r\nThe normal time to get a visa is 7 working days plus mail, which means \r\napprox. 2 weeks. The Russian embassy will stamp the visa direct into your passport \r\nand we feel it is both safer and more convenient for everyone that you send the paper\r\n to one of the many specialist travel companies in your country that deals with this.\r\nIf you have problems with your invitation paper or visa, please contact us \r\nImmediately.\r\n\r\n\r\n  You will need:  \r\n \r\n1. Russian invitation.\r\n2. Questionnaire form must to be filled out and signed at the bottom. You can \r\n  download this questionnaire from your local consulate or travel agency web page.\r\n3. Your passport.\r\n4. Four Passport photos (with some embassies it is enough with two.\r\n\r\nThe Russian visa application form will require you to confirm that you have \r\nboth travel insurance and medical evacuation cover valid in Russia.\r\n\r\nPlease double check your passport and visa in plenty of time before departure from \r\nyour country. Remember a passport must be valid for six months after date \r\nof planned departure from Russia. Your visa must have your name exactly as it is \r\nwritten in your passport and the dates in your visa must cover your entire visit to \r\nRussia. If these details are not correct, you could be refused entry into Russia.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWe are traveling to Murmansk. \r\n\r\n\r\n Our representative will meet you in the Airport or railway station and arrange \r\na further transport to the camp. If you arrive earlier or later we can arrange a \r\nprivate transport for you. \r\n\r\nBy airplane \r\n\r\n1. Helsinki (Finland) – Murmansk, our bus to the river\r\n \r\n2. Helsinki – Rovaniemi (Finland), our bus to the river\r\n\r\n2. Saint Petersburg – Murmansk, our bus to the river\r\n\r\n  For info contact – http://www.pulkovo.dk/ \r\n\r\n3. Moscow – Murmansk, our bus to the river\r\n\r\n  For info contact – http://www.aeroflot.ru/eng/\r\n\r\nBy train\r\n\r\n1. Saint Petersburg – Murmansk (to Murmansk city or to Kandalaksha station),\r\n  our bus to the river\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAll about it - in Blog Archive \\ April 2010',1,'2011-01-01 16:33:13','2011-01-01 16:33:13'),(41,'Huco taimen fishing.','<b> All about taimen  fishing - in our <a href=\"http://blog.chavanga.com\">Chavanga Blog</a>. </b>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.chavanga.com/2011/01/huco-taimen.html\">Hucho taimen. Part 1. Habarovsk region, Russia.</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.chavanga.com/2011/01/huco-taimen-fishing-part-2.html\">Hucho taimen fishing. Part 2</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.chavanga.com/2011/01/huco-taimen-fishing-part-3.html\">Hucho taimen fishing. Part 3.</a>\r\n\r\n<p align=center>\r\n<img src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_1bVgby4N7Wk/TR-G9quI5UI/AAAAAAAAAvs/g7xpRQjReBo/s400/%25D0%25A2%25D1%2583%25D0%25B3%25D1%2583%25D1%2580%2Braw36.jpg\" />\r\n<img src=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_1bVgby4N7Wk/TR-GOwf6N3I/AAAAAAAAAvc/fdbjFpXBgSs/s400/11111.jpg\"/>\r\n<img src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_1bVgby4N7Wk/TR-FXlhIdlI/AAAAAAAAAus/eFoO22WjvJA/s400/4.jpg\"/>\r\n<img src=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_1bVgby4N7Wk/TSBa_s5s9CI/AAAAAAAAAw8/Z26TYpPlp8s/s400/2.jpg\"/>\r\n<img src=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_1bVgby4N7Wk/TUQFAx1rGdI/AAAAAAAAAzs/2d3JSE8Ukb8/s400/222.jpg\"/>\r\n</p>',1,'2011-01-02 11:15:37','2011-02-26 16:52:42'),(42,'All articles about fishing - in Blog archives','You can read all articles during 2010 - 2011 years in Blog archives, not only on Main Page of site. \r\n<p align=center><a href=\"http://blog.chavanga.com/search?updated-min=2011-01-01T00%3A00%3A00%2B02%3A00&updated-max=2012-01-01T00%3A00%3A00%2B02%3A00&max-results=8\">2011</a> <a href=\"http://blog.chavanga.com/search?updated-min=2010-01-01T00%3A00%3A00%2B02%3A00&updated-max=2011-01-01T00%3A00%3A00%2B02%3A00&max-results=8\">2010</a></p>\r\nPlease, push \" ..read more...\" on our <a href=\"http://chavanga.com\">home page</a> to get into Blog Archives. \r\n\r\n<p align=center>\r\n[125]\r\n[114]\r\n[541]\r\n</p>',1,'2011-01-14 14:40:13','2011-02-26 16:45:56'),(43,'Huco taimen fishing in our program 4.','Taimen fishing is one of the most exotic and inaccessible directions in fishing. \r\n\r\nAll three small articles  \"Huco taimen fishing\" \r\nPart 1, 2, 3 are published to give on purpose to you a necessary minimum of the information on this fish and conditions of its fishing. Despite remoteness of this territory, its extensiveness and inaccessibility, here there is no possibility to accept tourists in unlimited quantity. Therefore, preparation for such tours is spent beforehand. \r\n\r\nPlaces in fishing commands, routes, the personnel and means are reserved in advance. In spite of the fact that the program on the river Tugur already is completely filled, I am glad to inform you that we still have possibility to provide a trip for 3 commands on the river Bichy. \r\n<p align=center>\r\n[136]\r\n[133]\r\n</p>\r\nIt is one of the best rivers of Khabarovsk territory for taimen fishing. Character of the river allows to fish with comfort already from the end of June. \r\n\r\nSpecify details you can using the information  <a href=\"http://chavanga.com/contact\">Contacts</a> on our site. \r\n\r\nThanks!\r\n<p align=center>\r\n[131]\r\n</p>',1,'2011-02-05 18:56:13','2011-02-26 16:40:24'),(44,'New offer for big salmon and huge trout fanats!','\r\nI want to inform you that  we offer you also some northern rivers of pool of Barents sea. Under the arrangement with company Sportfish we are engaged in working out of new camp on river Penka which is located with more known river Varzina. \r\n<b>It is the new project. </b>\r\n\r\nIn 2010 the first test fishing on the river has been organized, the place for camp is found. Since July, 2011 the standard camp on 6 fishers will work. \r\n\r\nThe additional information with the description of the river and about work of camp you can find in the Chavanga Blog. \r\nDelivery by helicopter, cost 1250 Euro from Murmansk. This very interesting offer for fans of a large salmon and a trout.  \r\n\r\n<p align=center>\r\n[480]\r\n[146]\r\n[135]\r\n</p>',1,'2011-02-17 15:04:06','2011-02-26 16:36:53'),(45,'A lot of images','You can find up to 500+ images at out gallery!\r\nvisit it now!\r\n<a href=http://chavanga.com/image_gallery_groups/3>Gallery</a>\r\n<p align=center>\r\n<img src= http://chavanga.com/images/fishing/p6/North%20Kola/4.jpg width=500 />\r\n\r\n<img src=http://chavanga.com/images/gallery/Chavanga%20best/spring/15.jpg width=500  />\r\n\r\n[98]\r\n[561]\r\n[352]\r\n[263]\r\n\r\n</p>',1,'2011-02-25 21:43:17','2011-02-26 14:20:38'),(46,'New Photos At \"The Best\" Album','A lot of new photos from different times:\r\n\r\nFrom <a href=\"http://chavanga.com/image_gallery_groups/69\">2006</a>\r\n<p align=center>\r\n[622]\r\n[620]\r\n</p>\r\n\r\nFrom <a href=\"http://chavanga.com/image_gallery_groups/70\">2007</a>\r\n<p align=center>\r\n[630]\r\n</p>\r\n\r\nFrom <a href=\"http://chavanga.com/image_gallery_groups/71\">2008</a>\r\n<p align=center>\r\n[632]\r\n[631]\r\n</p>\r\n\r\nFrom <a href=\"http://chavanga.com/image_gallery_groups/72\">2009</a>\r\n<p align=center>\r\n[650]\r\n[655]\r\n[642]\r\n</p>\r\n\r\nFrom <a href=\"http://chavanga.com/image_gallery_groups/68\">2010</a>\r\n<p align=center>\r\n[593]\r\n[597]\r\n[572]\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\nSee more at <a href=\"http://chavanga.com/image_gallery_groups/59\">The BEST Album</a>',1,'2011-02-27 22:13:08','2011-02-27 22:13:08'),(47,'Photo Gallery FancyBoxed!','Our gallery now use special <b>FancyBox</b> image resizer!\r\nSee it right now, just click on image and find out how images enlarge to you!\r\nVisit <a href=\"http://chavanga.com/image_gallery_groups/3\">Gallery</a>, and try it. it is fascinating!\r\n\r\nOur team thinks, that user friendly interface can improve your interest in fishing.\r\n\r\n<p align=center>\r\n[631]\r\n[599]\r\n</p>',1,'2011-02-28 21:44:14','2011-02-28 21:49:11'),(48,'All season trout and salmon fishing! North Kola programs.',' New offers! North Kola programs! Wild rivers, salmon and huge trout fishing.  New for 2011!\r\n<p align=center>\r\n[669]\r\n[670]\r\n</p>\r\nSince this year we had an opportunity to organize fishing on the rivers of northern part of Kola peninsula. These are the rivers Penka, Kozel, Goose. Located absolutely near to well-known but expensive Varzina. These are new projects, therefore in a current of 2-3 years their cost will be low. The stationary camp on the river the Skin will be constructed and will start to work in the end of June. It will be standard on  serve camp ( guide, cook, kitchen e.c.) with delivery by helicopter from Murmansk. \r\nCost is minimum, on one fisherman, it will make no more 800 - 1000Euros.  Any additional expenses it is not required.\r\n<p align=center>\r\n[668]\r\n[667]\r\n[666]\r\n</p>\r\nI will work on the Penka river   19.07 – 29.07  and  17.08. – 04.09. 2011.\r\n\r\nIn the end of August there will be a unique possibility to visit and to fish in the basic camp on the river Varzina. It will be a fact-finding trip for our company, therefore cost for fisherman  are lowered about 8900 Euros in 3 - 4 times to 1200Euro 6 days fishing. A departure of the helicopter from Murmansk 27.08.  We can attach to group to 6 persons. \r\n\r\nJoin us, \r\nyours faithfully, Vasil Bykau.\r\n\r\nwww.chavanga.com\r\n\r\n',1,'2011-03-08 09:55:21','2011-03-10 10:57:04'),(50,'SALES REPRESENTATIVE - North Kola program  ','\r\n[668]\r\n\r\nNorth Kola program includes Varzina, Penka, Drozdovka, Sidorovka and  another rivers of Barenc Sea coast. Varzina river is well known salmon and trout destination. Penka river is very interesting   , big salmon and huge trout special new project.Now we can do it on a solid base.\r\nWell come, friends! \r\n\r\n\r\n[693]\r\n[449]\r\n\r\n\r\nPOLAND\r\n\r\nSALES REPRESENTATIVE: \r\nVasyl Bykau\r\nWarszawa, Saska 9A\r\nMagazine “Wedkarstwo moje hobby”\r\nTel: +375 297 815546 \r\nE-Mail: fishfly@mail.ru gazeta@wmh.pl   \r\nSkype: gibon800kg \r\nfacebook: Vasyl Bykau\r\nSite: www.chavanga.com www.wmh.pl',1,'2011-03-14 13:31:57','2011-03-14 13:31:57'),(53,'DVD Chavanga salmon fishing and Photo show Chavanga autumne 2011','  DVD Chavanga fishing. NEW Photo gallery 2011\r\n\r\n1.   \"W Krolewstwie Lososia\" film released. \r\n\r\n YouTube:\r\n <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=siPZkOTNnZM\">W Krolestwie Lososia</a>. <p style=\"text-align:center;\"> <img src=\"../../images/events/DVD Chavanga 2009.jpg\"/> </p>\r\nPlease see original version  on DVD wmh.pl\r\n\r\n2. Photo show Chavanga autumne 2011\r\n\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OrhA6zf9IyU&fmt=18',1,'2011-04-11 15:59:25','2011-12-01 21:23:57'),(64,'Salmon and trout fishing in Russia.  Strelna river. Mix Chavanga-Strelna tours.','Salmon fishing in Russia.                             The River Strelna tour\r\nThe river description\r\n\r\n[740]\r\n\r\nThis river is located in 50 km to the east from Chavanga river. Strelna is considered  as the large river, it is the fifth biggest river on Kola Peninsula. Certainly, the size of the river from the point of view of the fisherman, depends on season. The spring high water in the beginning of May, carries a large amount of water, but and in the middle of summer during dry time, it is a little water, and the river is accessible on all sites.\r\n\r\n [745]\r\n\r\nThe lower part of the river, close to the seaside is wide and spacious, with the very accessible banks. First half of mile from the seaside, the river flows through rock and mountains. Here are the set of picturesque rocks and falls. River banks are firm, rocky, covered with large stones and pebble. Water carries hardly a brownish, \"tea\" shade. But in a dry season water almost colourless. Futher  up the river, after all the  falls and rocks, the valley extends and  the river becomes quieter, stone rifts and fast current streams changing each other.\r\n\r\n [760]\r\n\r\nFishes\r\nThe Atlantic salmon and sea trout regularly comes into the river. These are the kinds of fish, fishermen coming here for. Plenty of graylings and a local brown trout who reaches the large sizes and quite interesting to catch for the fishermen.\r\nPopulation of a salmon in Strelna reaches the considerable sizes. The river is quite far from the closest local village so there is a minimal chance of poaching. As well as on other rivers running into the White sea, the fresh income of salmon becomes pretty usual thing. The biggest amount of fresh salmon is taken place in the autumn, September and the beginning of October and Spring in the end of May and first half of June. But there is also a summer course of a salmon, sometimes intensive enough. The largest fishes enter the river in the spring and from the end of August when it is possible to catch copies more than 10 kg in weight. But fish is in the river all season and at any time it is possible to catch a salmon. The prime- time for salmon is considered from 15th of May till 15th Of June. At this time the fish waits downstream from waterfalls. Therefore it is very convenient to fish directly near camp, within the lower part of the river. This time also estimated more expensive. The second peak of salmon fishing comes in September. From first weeks of September, autumn fish, which differs special physical standards, begin to come to the river. \r\n\r\n[784]\r\n         Separate interest is represented by fishing the sea trout. The sea trout here is a the typical sea form of silver colouring and the local form which differs brown colouring and large black stains. During the best time when high water falls down, trout of 2-3 kg come across, large fishes to 4-4.5 kg in weight are considered. The end of June - July are considered as the best time for fishing the large trout. In August the size of a trout begins to decrease, but at this time, fresh salmon comes to the river increasing the population of sea trout. By the end of August, and in September fishing the trout goes on recession. Therefore as the best time for hunting for a large trout consider the end of June - July.\r\nThus, it is possible to combine fishing the salmon and a trout or to choose purely trout variant in the middle of summer. \r\n\r\n[753]\r\n\r\nCamp\r\nThe camp Strelna is located in a picturesque place on Island in delta decks at the sea. Distance to the coast is around 300 metres, to the river - less than 100 metres. The camp consists of 4 wooden houses, in each of them 3 rooms for clients, shower, toilet, a room for drying and the furnace are located. Each room accommodate 2 fishermen. Houses are equipped by electric heating of water. The dining room is located in a separate structure, the lunch hall is equipped with fireplace, bar with alcoholic drinks, TV and others. Nearby, there is a kitchen. The spacious bath with a sweating room is constructed here, on river bank. \r\n\r\nThe fishing organisation\r\nTerms\r\nThe fishing season opens since May, 15th. The season end legally is not limited, depending on weather conditions it is possible to finish a season in the middle of October.  \r\nCapacity\r\nThe camp contains up to 10 fishermen. The standard group at the beginning of the season is 10 persons. In the middle of a season, groups usually consists of 8 persons. Groups with smaller quantity of participants are accepted after the coordination of details with the organizer of tour.\r\n Duration of tour\r\nStandard tour is consider as  6 + days  of fishing. Recommended day of arrival and departure is Saturday. \r\nUnder individual demands duration of tour can be prolonged or reduced. \r\nTransfer\r\n\r\nThe camp is in 50 km to the east from Chavanga river. Approximately the distance from Varzuga mouth makes about 90 km. From Umba river, the distance is around 230 km.\r\nTo get to the Strelna camp is possible by the helicopter, by the truck or the powerboat by the sea.\r\nThe approximate plan of  transfer looks so:\r\n1.	The Variant. Meeting at the airport of Murmansk. Delivery by a minibus to Umba takes  5 hours. Road to the mouth of Varzuga takes 3.5 hours by the off-road car. Then 3 hours to the river Chavanga and then  2.5 hours to Strelna. It  is considerate as  inexpensive and a reliable variant. \r\n2.	The Variant. Meeting at the airport of Murmansk. Delivery by a minibus to Umba takes  5 hours. Road to the mouth of Varzuga takes 3.5 hours by the off-road car. Then by the powerboat to Strelna takes 1.5 - 2 hours. It is an inexpensive and convenient variant. This method of trasportation depends on weather conditions on the sea.  \r\n3.	The Variant. Meeting at the airport of Murmansk. Delivery by a minibus to Umba takes 5 hours. Than from Umba there is  1 hour flight by helicopter straight to Strelna camp. It is comfortable enough and fast way of delivery. A bit more expensive way of traveling.\r\n4.  The Variant is a mix of helicopter  (way to or back way ) and  off-road car. Meeting at the airport of Murmansk. Delivery by a minibus to Umba takes 5 hours. Than from Umba there is  1 hour flight by helicopter straight to Strelna camp. Back way we start by  the off-road car,  minibus from Umba to Murmansk.\r\nThe tour includes:\r\n1.	Residing at camp of 7 nights\r\n2.	З-х a single food\r\n3.	Cost of fishing licences\r\n4.	Using a camp infrastructure - dryers, a bath, a chimney hall, the TV\r\n5.	Services of the cook and the guide\r\n6.	6 days of fishing\r\n\r\nTour doesn’t include:\r\n1.    Transfer from Murmansk to camp and back\r\n2.	Alcohol\r\n3.     Insurance\r\n4.	The Visa help\r\n\r\n\r\n  Salmon and trout fishing in Russia.\r\n  Mix  Chavanga -  Strelna rivers tour.\r\n\r\n\r\n We offer you the mixed programs including fishing on the river Chavanga and on the river Strelna.\r\nIt allows you:\r\n1.	Visiting 2 rivers, which have different character, conditions and fishing behavior, in one program tour.\r\n2.	Allows to break a transfer from Murmansk into 2 parts, that makes the time spend during transfer more enjoyable.\r\n3.	It is possible to prolong duration of tour from 6-7 nights to 9 or 10 nights, which is difficult to make on a one river tour.\r\n4.	It is possible to make tour individual, choosing the river with the best conditions for the period of tour.\r\n5.	It is possible to choose the most convenient time and a way of a transfer for movement between camps of Chavanga and Strelna. It is possible to begin with fishing  on Chavange, then to visit Strelna or on the contrary that reduces time of a continuous transfer.\r\n6.	Choosing the mixed program, it is easier to organise non-standard groups.\r\n7.	It is possible to make the program answering to financial inquiries of clients.\r\nThe mixed programs usually include some days of fishing on the river Chavanga and some days on Strelna. Usually, these programs are popular in the middle of a season when they become more accessible at the price. Their basic advantage is possibility to correct the program on a place, having prolonged or having reduced fishing terms on Chavange or on Strelna. Here it is possible to consider an individual condition of the river directly during tour.\r\n\r\nCost of standard tour on the river Strelna\r\nCost is defined by cost of standard tour calculated for 8 persons and cost of additional services, mainly - a transfer from a place of an arrival to base. \r\n1.	Salmon tour.\r\nThe best time for fishing the salmon is from 15.05 till 15.06 and in the autumn from 10.09 till 15.10  is …….. Euros from the person plus transfer cost. That is the cost of standard tour for standard group of 8 persons makes ………….. Euros plus cost of a transfer for all group.\r\n2.	The Mixed salmon and trout programs in the middle of a season is low - …… Euros from the client plus transfer cost. \r\nGroups with quantity of clients less than 8 persons pay extra the missing amount to cost of standard tour.\r\nCost of the mixed programs \r\nCost of the mixed programs is calculated at cost of actual days of fishing on the rivers Chavanga and Strelna. The price depends on the program of tour and is co-ordinated with the organizer.\r\nBooking and payment conditions\r\nPlaces and tour time are considered reserved for as clients after the coordination of all details with the organizer and a guarantee of payment of tour.  \r\nThe down payment makes 30 % from a total cost of tour and is brought by cash or on the bill of the organizer not later than 01.03 current years. The overall cost is paid to the organizer on a place, on arrival to a catching place.\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1,'2011-09-05 14:08:51','2012-02-13 13:57:30'),(69,'Future salmon population. Kola Peninsula salmon fishing next 2012-2015 years','\r\n       Really, number of salmons in the rivers can be predicted. As a basis it is possible to take the data of calculation of real quantity of fishes in the rivers. With some share of objectivity it can be made there where there are special counters of fishes which come into the rivers. If we have such data for some years then it is possible to argue with some confidence on the future season.\r\n        As a whole the quantity of salmons in the river depends on set of factors. The negative factors - most known to us it is fishing pressure and poaching. But these factors concern adult population of fishes which never reached on our rivers of hundreds thousand or millions fishes. Therefore major factors which add or take away thousand and millions fishes  are spawning and the sea period of life of a salmon. Unsuccessful for  spawning river condotion  or catastrophic winter and fast spring high waters reduce population of next years by thousand. The adverse situation in the sea also can lead to loss of tens and hundreds thousand young salmons which have put to sea from the rivers. In my opinion, it is major factors which can cardinally change number of salmons in the rivers.\r\n\r\nread more....\r\nhttp://blog.chavanga.com/2011/12/future-salmon-population-kola-peninsula.html',1,'2012-02-06 09:43:39','2012-02-06 09:43:39'),(71,'New youtube video. Chavanga salmon  fishing','<p align=center>\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/51989039?badge=0\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe> \r\n</p><hr size=1 /><p align=center>\r\n<iframe width=\"320\" height=\"240\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/TK7Jwqswohw\" frameborder=\"1\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n</p><hr size=1 /><p align=center>\r\n<iframe width=\"320\" height=\"240\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/siPZkOTNnZM\" frameborder=\"1\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n</p><hr size=1 /><p align=center>\r\n<iframe width=\"320\" height=\"240\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/SohIezgK9mo\" frameborder=\"1\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n</p><hr size=1 /><p align=center>\r\n<iframe width=\"320\" height=\"240\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/z0aoHyULgcg\" frameborder=\"1\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n</p><hr size=1 /><p align=center>\r\n<iframe width=\"320\" height=\"240\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/OrhA6zf9IyU\" frameborder=\"1\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n</p><hr size=1 /><p align=center>\r\n<iframe width=\"320\" height=\"240\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/GySaeueNihY\" frameborder=\"1\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n</p><hr size=1 /><p align=center>\r\n<iframe width=\"320\" height=\"240\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/5jFJBxpU8gI\" frameborder=\"1\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n</p><hr size=1 /><p align=center>\r\n<iframe width=\"320\" height=\"240\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/7hMbQeRBmu4\" frameborder=\"1\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n</p><hr size=1 /><p align=center>\r\n<iframe width=\"320\" height=\"240\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/caK7iPbGWaQ\" frameborder=\"1\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\nNice photo album  is here:\r\n\r\nhttp://issuu.com/pool32mag/docs/pool_32_mag_no._4',1,'2012-02-11 08:42:03','2013-04-21 12:39:45'),(100,'Wild rainbows program. New information!!!','In the coming days I will post all the information about our new program for catching trophy wild rainbow trout. I will start with a description of the river, give information about fish and the methods of fishing trout, and then introduce you to the organization of fishing and introduce you to the base. This is a new and very interesting route. I\'m sure you will like it!\r\n\r\n1.river description\r\n2.camp \r\n3.fishing organization\r\n4.rainbows\r\n5.chars family\r\n\r\nnext - \r\n\r\n6.pacific salmon\r\n7.flies and methods',1,'2014-10-22 09:26:29','2014-11-01 09:01:31'),(102,'New photo albums!!','I am very pleased to introduce you to a few photos. that made our friends, great anglers Fabrizio, Mateus and Flavio. In the pictures you can see the river Chavanga late fall of this year.\r\n\r\nAlbums can be found on the main page or on these links.\r\n\r\n{{http://blog.chavanga.com/2014/10/prime-week-october-surprise.html}}\r\n\r\n{{http://blog.chavanga.com/2014/11/the-end-of-season-2014-extra-fabrizio.html}}\r\n\r\n[990]\r\n\r\n\r\nAll the best!!!\r\n\r\n',1,'2014-11-15 10:24:36','2014-12-07 20:32:29');
