INSERT INTO `fishing_programs` VALUES (1,'Chavanga river salmon tour','Chavanga\\nriver','2010-02-13 20:07:05','2013-12-22 20:50:46','<h2 class=\'fishing_tour_name\'>Chavanga river</h2>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>The tour description.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n\r\nSalmon fishing in Russia. Kola Peninsula.\r\nChavanga it is the river of a southeast part of Kola peninsula, it runs into \r\nthe White sea in 60 km on the east from the mouth of Varzuga river. \r\nThis is a territory of ‘’Belomorska’’ tundra. \r\nThere is no blazed road, on the coast there is more or less appreciable track, on \r\nseacoast, through the rocks approaching directly to the sea. \r\nTime in a way approximately 3 hours by off-road-car. \r\nThe variant with a powerboat is more comfortable, it goes to Chavanga less than \r\nhour, but it depends on the sea condition, which is really important. \r\nBecause of the hard connectivity to the river there is a minimum amount of people \r\nfishing there which is make our fishing trip as good as we dreamt about it. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nIn the mouth of the river there is a village with the same name as river, there \r\nis also a mail and a shop. The river of the average sizes, a water level, as well \r\nas on other rivers, depends on a season and weather. The spring high water happens \r\nconsiderable enough, the water level rises about 100cm and above. In the middle of \r\nsummer and in the autumn all depends on weather, level fluctuates depending on \r\npassing rains. The herd of salmon has not suffered yet from fishing pressure. \r\nThe average size of a salmon here is 3-4 kg. It is conditionally possible to \r\nallocate 3 streams of salmon, spring in May - June, less intensive summer and \r\nautumn course from second half of September. The great bulk of spring salmon is \r\nmade by fishes of average weight, from 3 kg and above. But often there are big \r\nexamples of 5-6 kg. The fish of 7-8 kg, basically concern autumn or early spring \r\ncalling.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nIn Chavanga there is a big chance to catch a good trout as well. There are 2 \r\nforms - a through passage and settled trout. Depending on a season and a fishing \r\nplace one of these forms prevails. A good trout Trophy you can catch is around \r\n2.5-3 kg. Chavanga is one of the best rivers of southern coast on population of \r\ngraylings. This fish meets from the moment of a descent of ice and till global \r\nicing in late autumn. The standard size is 40-48 cm. Grayling more than 50 cm are \r\nnot so rare as well.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe river is unique, available and convenient for fly fishing during whole season. \r\nThe total length of the river to the falls is 17 km and each part is accessible and \r\ninteresting for fishing. Conditionally, the character of the river can be divided \r\ninto <b>3 parts</b>.\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\n<b>1st part</b> begins from the sea, passes a number of rocky exits and falls, leaves on \r\nan extensive reach and proceeds in a twisting stony bed. Total length of the first \r\nsite is 6 km. This is a good place for fishing in the first half of season, in June \r\nand the beginning of July, and also in the end of a season, in second half of \r\nSeptember, when it is calling fresh salmon from the sea. The beginning of the river \r\nis very interesting for fishing a through passage trout, especially in the second \r\nhalf of summer and in the autumn. Above small falls is a excellent places for \r\ngrayling fly fishing, the best time is the first half of season. \r\n</li>\r\n<br/>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\n<b>2nd part</b> is located above, has more flat character. Its length is also \r\naround 6-7 km. Flat coast are convenient for fishing during the periods of high \r\nwater. Here it is a lot of places for spawning and salmon remains all season. \r\nDuring the big water lots of trout and grayling crowding together and becomes \r\nreally active at this time, and its makes our fishing very exciting.\r\n</li>\r\n<br/>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\n<b>3rd site</b> gradually enters into a rocky canyon with the high coast which \r\nhave grown with the forest. Here the river comes to an end, because of a big \r\nfalls which is too high for salmon. It is the least visited part of the river, \r\nhere is always a big chance to catch trophy fish. In the middle of summer a water \r\ntemperature here usually less on 2-3 degrees than in lower parts of the river. \r\nIt positively affects activity of fishes, especially in hot days in the middle \r\nof summer. Here is the largest population of graylings. \r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nFishing on Chavange is organised as well as on other salmon rivers under licences. \r\nThere are <b>3 camps</b> created for guests. \r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\n1st camp. There is House of the Fisherman for 6 or 7 persons. There are 2 guest \r\nrooms, kitchen, refrigerator, TV and sauna. The conditions are really comfortable \r\nfor any accidents, like cold and rainy days especially at the beginnings of June \r\nand the end of September. \r\n</li>\r\n<br/>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\n2nd camp. There is camp on a river bank which is on a grassy meadow the camp \r\ncalled ’’Pokosi’’. \r\n</li>\r\n<br/>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\n3rd camp. There is a camp located on the bank of the river. The camp \r\ncalled ‘’Top’’ which is in 4 km from the falls. \r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\nFor a comfortable mobility trips, the cross-country vehicle is provided. \r\nIt allows you to enjoy the river easily and try on all 3 sites. \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\nDepending on a season and personal preferences it is possible to choose the \r\nvariant of camping and fishing.\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\n<b>Optimum line-up is 6 persons.</b> But the quantity of participants is not limited and \r\nit is possible to make the group from 2 to 8 persons. \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\n<b>Tours season starts - from 03.06 till 01.10. 2010</b>\r\n</p>\r\n<br/>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Standard tour includes:</b> placing on one of the camps \r\n(the House of the Fisherman, camp ‘’Pokosi’’ or ‘’Top’’) and 6 or 7 days of \r\nfishing. Depending on desire of clients duration of round can be prolonged till \r\n10 days. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<b>The program of 6 days tour on 1st site.</b>\r\n<br/>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\n<b>1-2nd day</b>. A group meeting at the airport of Murmansk or railway station \r\nof Kandalaksha. If it is necessary, staying for a night in hotel of Kandalaksha \r\nor Murmansk or in the village Kuzomen in the mouth of Varzuga river. Delivery to \r\nthe Chavanga river and placing in the House of the Fisherman.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<b>3-4th day</b>. Fishing on the 1 camp of the river.\r\n</li>\r\n<b>5-7th day</b>. Fishing on 1-2 or 3rd camps of the river. Fishing is organised \r\nat desire of clients. 2, 3 or 4 trips on the cross-country vehicle to the top \r\nsites of the river are provided.\r\n<li>\r\n<b>8th day</b>. Fishing on 1 camp of the river.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<b>9th day</b>. Returning to the airport or railway station. \r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\nChanges can be made on the tour depending on fishing and river conditions. \r\nAdditional day of fishing can be given at guests desire. \r\n</p>\r\n<br/>\r\n<b>The tour price include:</b>\r\n<br/>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\nThe invitation and the voucher for visa reception. \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nRegistration, delivery from the airport of Murmansk or train station Kandalaksha and back. \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nAccommodation, sauna.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n3 meals a day during all tour, services of the cook.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nFishing guide.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nTransport for the movements on the river (off-road cars, the cross-country vehicle, \r\nmotor boats, a minibus). \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nCost of fishing licences.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nThe first medical aid.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n<b>Do not include: </b>\r\n<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\nInsurance.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nCost of tickets to the meeting point (airplane tickets).\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nAlcohol.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',4,1),(2,'Varzuga- Kitsa- Indiora cheap tours','Varzuga\\nKitsa\\nIndiora\\nrivers','2010-02-13 20:07:05','2013-12-22 20:51:13','<h2 class=\'fishing_tour_name\'>\r\nFishing round on the rivers Varzuga - Kitsa - Indera.\r\n</h2>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>The tour description.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n\r\nSalmon fishing in Russia.\r\nVarzuga – is one of the most known salmon rivers on Kola peninsula. \r\nIt is located in the southeast of Kola peninsula and runs into the \r\nWhite sea. The river possesses unique on number herd of an Atlantic \r\nsalmon. \r\nThe popularity is very famous among fisherman in the whole \r\nworld. The chance of catching the fish is extremely high. The season \r\nbegins early, right after an ice drift in May and proceeds to the late \r\nfall. Spinning catching is allowed , but the preference is given to \r\nthe fly fishing. As well as other rivers, Varzuga are changed by the \r\ncharacter depending on a season. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe end of May, right after an ice \r\ndescent, is marked by intensive calling of a fresh sea salmon. At a \r\nhigh water level some advantages has spinning fishing as well. Fish \r\nattacks baits very actively and this attracts many fishermans. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nBy the end of June water in the river falls, catching becomes more \r\nconveniently because activity of fish is decreasing a little. In \r\nmany respects the water level depends on weather. Fishing is \r\norganized by a principle: caught and released. Special licence \r\nsites are organized on the banks of the rivers to make your fishing \r\neasier. Except salmon there is grayling, corigonus and a trout. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nAccommodation is offered in the house of the fisherman which is in \r\nthe village Varzuga located on both river banks in 17 km from the \r\nsea. The bed linen, 3 meals per day, sauna is provided, rooms for \r\n2-3 person. Delivery to a catching place is made on a motor boat \r\naccompanied by the guide.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe river Kitsa is an inflow of Varzuga river. They merge together \r\nin 2 kilometres from the sea. Kitsa is not so wide as Varzuga, it \r\nis more twisted аnd thresholded . Here too the intensive course of \r\na salmon is observed and chances to catch large grayling and a trout \r\nare very good. Kitsa runs in Varzugu just opposite to village and \r\nfishers deliver to a place лова on motor boats. Catching is carried \r\nout as well as on Varzuge by a principle has caught? Has released on \r\nlicence sites. As in Kuzomen there is no good road, on Kitse there \r\nare less than fishers, is especially quiet in the middle of summer \r\nand is closer by the autumn. Fishers deliver in Kuzomen on the \r\noff-road car. Time in a way from village Varzuga makes about 40 \r\nminutes. Residing is organised to picturesque village Kuzomen in \r\nthe house of the local fisher. Visitors are provided with 3 single \r\nfood, there is a sauna. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe river Indera is small in comparison with Kitsej and the more so \r\nwith Varzugoj. Nevertheless, it is very picturesque river, running \r\ninto the sea in 10 km. From a mouth of Varzugi. In the river there \r\nis a herd of salmons, but it is more interesting to catch here a sea \r\ntrout and large хариуса. Fishers deliver to the river on the off-road \r\ncar from a mouth of Varzugi. Time in a way about 30 minutes. \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Duration of round</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nTrip is well-organized, for fishing on each river is expected to be \r\ntwo - three days. The total days of fishing is 6 or 7 under the \r\npreliminary arrangement.\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Group structure</p>\r\nOptimum structure of group is 5 person. The maximum number of \r\nparticipants is 6 persons.\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSeason of trips starts - from 03.06 till the end of october. \r\n\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>The program 6 days rounds.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<b>1st day</b>. A meeting at the airport of Murmansk or station Kandalaksha. Delivery to village Varzuga and placing in the house. Supper. Survey of sights.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<b>2 and 3rd day</b>. Fishing on the river Varzuga.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<b>4 and 5th day</b>. Moving on the river Kitsu. Placing in village Kuzomen. Departing to the fishing camp.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<b>6th day</b>. A trip to the river Indera. Returning to village Kuzomen.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<b>7th day</b>. Fishing on the river Kitsa (or at will of clients on Varzuga river).\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<b>8th day</b>. Returning to the airport or railway station. \r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\nChanges can be made to a trip route depending on a condition of the \r\nrivers and fishing conditions. At will of clients equivalent \r\nreplacement of places of fishing is given. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Into trip cost include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\nInvitation and the voucher for visa reception. \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nRegistration.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nDelivery from the airport of Murmansk or from rail station Kandalaksha and back.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nResiding, sauna\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n3 single meal/day during all trip\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nServices of the fishing guide and food chief.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nTransport for  the movements on the rive (off-road cars, the cross-country vehicle, motor boats, a minibus)\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nCost of fishing licences.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nFirst medical aid.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Do not include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\nInsurance\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nCost of tickets to the meeting point (airplane tickets)\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nAlcohol\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',8,1),(3,'East Kola rivers tour','Pulonga\\nPialitsa\\nChapoma\\nrivers','2010-02-13 20:07:05','2013-12-22 20:52:58','<h2 class=\'fishing_tour_name\'>\r\nFishing trip to the rivers: Pulonga - Pjalitsa-Chapoma.\r\n</h2>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>The tour description.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n\r\nSalmon fishing in Russia.\r\nThese rivers are in the southeast of Kola peninsula and run into \r\nthe White sea. All of them cut rocky files and in the bottom part \r\nproceed on territory of Belomorsky tundra. The coast in Pulonga \r\narea is not occupied, in the mouth of rivers Pjalitsa and Chapoma \r\nsmall fishing villages are located. Character of the rivers depends \r\non a season. Largest of them is Chapoma. The river has comfortable \r\nfor catching pre-mouth site in length about 3 km, then the river \r\nleaves in rocky gorge. There is the highest Kola peninsula falls. \r\nThe season beginning from the first half of June and characterised \r\nby high water level. \r\n<br />\r\nThis period is an intensive calling of the Atlantic salmon. Average \r\nweight of fish is 3.5-5 kg. In the middle of summer the water level \r\nfalls, reaching a minimum in August. This is a fine and comfortable \r\ntime for catching summer salmon, sea trout and brown trout. From the \r\nmiddle of September the course of a salmon from the sea amplifies \r\nagain, reaching a maximum by the end of September, the beginning of \r\nOctober. The river Pjalitsa proceeds in 30 km to the east of Chapoma. \r\nIt is rather small river, and for catching salmon the most interesting \r\nis the beginning of the season, the period of high water. But fish is \r\nwell caught also in the middle of summer and in August. There is no \r\ngraylings, but the large sea trout happens to be caught and sometimes \r\nin a big amount.\r\n<br />\r\nOn the east in 23 km from Pjalitsy the river Pulonga farthest and \r\nthe seldom visited river from our round is located. The maximum \r\nquantity of water and fresh fish is necessary for June. But also \r\nin the middle of summer calling of a salmon though the river loses \r\nin sizes for fans of salmon fishing a little proceeds. Second half \r\nof July and August perfectly approach for catching of a sea trout. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nRound is well-organized, for fishing on each river we taking one or \r\ntwo days depending on weather conditions and wishes of clients. \r\nDuring the period of ‘’The white nights’’ From June till August \r\ntime of fishing during one day is not limited.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nMovement is proceeding on the special off-road car or a powerboat. \r\nThis trip is very interesting, it gives to fishermen a maximum of \r\nimpressions, but simultaneously demands from participants of certain \r\nphysical preparation and discipline.\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Accommodation.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOn the rivers Pulonga and Pjalitsa there is a camp and a kitchen. \r\nTents and sleeping bags are given. On the river Chapoma accommodation \r\norganized in the village house, the linen and a sauna is provided. \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Duration of round.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nNormal round includes 6 days of fishing.\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Group structure.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOptimum structure of group is 5 persons. The maximum number of \r\nparticipants is 6 persons.\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Terms of the season.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nSeason begins - from 10.06.2011 till 25.09.2011\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe program of standard 6 day rounds.\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\n<b>1-2 day</b>. A group meeting at the airport of Murmansk or \r\nrailway station of Kandalaksha. If it is necessary staying for \r\nthe night in hotel of Kandalaksha or Murmansk or in a village \r\nKuzomen in moutha of the river Varzuga. Delivery to a catching \r\nplace on the river Pulonga in 150 km from Kuzomeni. Placing in a \r\ncamp.\r\n</li>\r\n<br/>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\n<b>3-4th day</b>. Fishing on the river.\r\n</li>\r\n<br/>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\n<b>5-6th day</b>. Departure on the river Pjalitsa. Placing in a \r\ncamp. Fishing.\r\n</li>\r\n<br/>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\n<b>6-7th day</b>. Departure on the river Chapoma. Placing in the \r\nvillage house. Fishing. Sauna.\r\n</li>\r\n<br/>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\n<b>8-9th day</b>. Returning to village Kuzomen and delivery to the \r\nairport or on a railway station. If it is necessary staying for the \r\nnight in village Kuzomen or in hotel of Kandalaksha or Murmansk.\r\n</li>\r\n<p>\r\nThe round program can be changed at will of clients and depending \r\non fishing conditions of the river, for example, from a water level.\r\n</p>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>The tour price include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\nInvitation and the voucher for visa reception.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nRegistration.\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\nDelivery from the airport of Murmansk or from the train station \r\nKandalaksha to a place of catching and back on a minibus and an off-road car.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nAccommodation, sauna.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n3 meals every day during all round.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nServices of the driver and the fishing guide.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nTransport on a catching place (the cross-country vehicle, motor \r\nboats) - fishing licenses.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nThe first medical aid.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Do not include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\nInsurance\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nCost of tickets to the meeting point (airplane tickets)\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nAlcohol\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',12,1),(4,'Taimen fishing. Habarovsk region','Habarovsk region','2010-02-13 20:07:05','2013-12-22 20:53:00','<p align=\'center\'><h2 class=\'fishing_tour_name\'>The Bichy river</h2></p>\r\n<h3 class=\'fishing_river_title\'>For a Siberian taimen (hucho taimen)</h3>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe alloy on an average current of the river  Bichy. The river is small, convenient for catching. This is the most comfortable  flyfishing  taimen trip. With itself it is necessary to take the personal things packed in a  hermetic   bag, tackles, sleeping bags. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Trophies:</b> taimen,   lenoks, Arctic grayling,  Amur pike,   Siberian salmon. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Terms:</b> from June, 1st till October, 15th.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Group:</b> 6 persons. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Residing conditions:</b> an alloy by boats, one boat and guide/ 2 rods, a camp, boat for bags and tackles, 4 places tents/ 2 rods. .     It is necessary to take personal packed in hermetic bags, tackles, sleeping bags.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Duration of fishing:</b> at will of fishermen. Recommended duration of fishing is 7 days. \r\n</p>\r\n1st day: Arrival in Khabarovsk airport. Moving Khabarovsk- Tambovka (the bus. 8 hours), probably to order the helicopter from Khabarovsk. In the presence of good weather a start on the river (helicopter MI-8. 1 hour of 30 mines), fishing. \r\n<br/>\r\n2nd- 7th days: the alloy, fishing. \r\n<br/>\r\n8th day: fishing, gathering, the helicopter to Tambovka, the bus to Khabarovsk. A start from Khabarovsk.\r\n</br>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Cost of a package from Khabarovsk to Khabarovsk:</b> ………………. from one fisherman (at group not less than 6 persons).\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Into cost enters:</b> a meeting-seeing-off, transport expenses, the guide (1 guide/2 rods), the cook, a food, the equipment and equipment, the license. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Into cost does not enter:</b> hotel accommodation, payment of additional luggage, insurance, spirits, a satellite communication, other services which have been not provided by the preliminary arrangement.\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\'center\'><h2 class=\'fishing_tour_name\'>The river Tugur</h2></p>\r\n<h3 class=\'fishing_river_title\'>For a Siberian taimen(hucho taimen)</h3>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\nIt is sparsely populated, remote area. The largest rivers (Uda and Tugur) proceed on boggy valleys and have close to flat character. On the contrary, many of their inflows    present mountain rivers. In Ude and Tugure till now is a lot of large Siberian taimen. Uniqueness of these herds tajmen consists that it can eat numerous here a Siberian salmon. The forage abundance allows a predator to reach the huge sizes. There are authentic data on capture here fishes in weight in 70 and even 95 kgs! And more than 30 kgs here catch fishes in weight annually. Except taimen, lenoks, Amur graylings, sig-hadary and the Amur pike are interesting for fishers.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Trophies:</b> taimen, lenoks, since August, 1st a Siberian salmon (salmons through passage). \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Terms:</b> from June, 1st till October, 10th. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Group:</b> 6 persons.\r\n</p> \r\n\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Residing conditions:</b> an alloy by boats, one boat and guide/ 2 rods, a camp, boat for bags and tackles, 4 places tents/ 2 rods.     It is necessary to take personal packed in hermetic bags, tackles, sleeping bags.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Duration of fishing:</b> at will of fishermen. Recommended duration of fishing is 7 days. \r\n</p>\r\n1st day: Arrival in Khabarovsk airport.  The trip from Khabarovsk to  Briakan (the bus. 15 hours-660 km) \r\n<br/>\r\n2nd day: In the presence of flight weather we will  start on the river (helicopter MI-8, 1 hour of 15 mines), fishing. \r\n</br>\r\n3rd, 4th, 5th, 6th, 7th day: an alloy, fishing. \r\n</br>\r\n8th day:   helicopter to Briakana,   car to Khabarovsk .   Start from Khabarovsk airport.\r\n\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Cost of a package from Khabarovsk to Khabarovsk:</b>…………….. from one fisherman (at group not less than 6 persons). \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Into cost enters:</b> a meeting, a seeing-off, transport expenses, the guide, the cook, a food, the equipment and equipment, the license.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Into cost does not enter:</b> hotel accommodation, payment of additional luggage, insurance, spirits, a satellite communication, other services which have been not provided by the preliminary arrangement. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\'center\'><h2 class=\'fishing_tour_name\'>The rivers Ketanda and Urak</h2></p>\r\n<h3 class=\'fishing_river_title\'>The river of Pacific salmons</h3>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\nThe large river running in Ohotsky sea exhausting in 20 kilometers south-to the west of\r\nOhotsk town. Ketanda is a largest inflow Uraka running into it at the left in 83 kilometers from the sea. To get on Ketandu it is possible dragging from the river Judomy. It is possible to be thrown also here by helicopter from Ohotska. In the rivers it is a lot of fish-  Pacific salmons (silver salmon, a Siberian salmon and a humpback salmon, red salmon), char (Dolly Varden char and white spotted char) and large grayling which often happens in weight more than 2 kg.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Trophies:</b> coho salmon,  a Siberian salmon, red salmon, chars,   a humpback salmon, grayling. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Terms:</b> from July, 1st till September, 25th, including: since July, 15th a humpback salmon, red salmon; since August, 15th silver salmon, a Siberian salmon.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Group:</b> 6 persons.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Residing conditions:</b> an alloy by boats, one boat and guide/ 2 rods, a camp, boat for bags and tackles, 4 places tents/ 2 rods.     It is necessary to take personal packed in hermetic bags, tackles, sleeping bags.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Duration of fishing:</b> At will of fishermen. Recommended duration of fishing of 7 days.\r\n</p>\r\n1st day: arrival to Khabarovsk airport, night in hotel (cost of a hotel room 50 - 250 USD.)\r\n<br/>\r\n2nd day: a start to Ohotsk  town (3,5 hours of flight), arrival in Ohotsk, in the presence of flight weather - a start to Urak river (1.5 hours of the general touch), fishing. \r\n<br/>\r\n3rd, 4th, 5th, 6th, 7th days: an alloy, fishing \r\n<br/>\r\n8th day: fishing, a mouth of Urak river. The way   (car) to the river Hunting, a crossing through the river Hunting by boats, further a car to the   Airport (with a crossing through the river Hunting all it will occupy 3-4 hours).\r\n<br/>\r\n9th day:   start to Khabarovsk.  \r\n\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Round cost: Ohotsk-Ohotsk.</b> ……………….from one fisherman (at group not less than 6 persons). \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Into cost enters:</b> a meeting, a seeing-off in Ohotsk town, Khabarovsk,  helocopter, the guide, the cook, a food, the equipment and equipment, the licenses..\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>    \r\n<b>Into cost does not enter:</b> insurance, spirits, a satellite communication, other services which have been not provided by the preliminary arrangement.\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\'center\'><h2 class=\'fishing_tour_name\'>The river Uda and its inflows</h2></p>\r\n<h3 class=\'fishing_river_title\'>For a Siberian taimen (hucho taimen)</h3>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nIt is sparsely populated, remote area. In Ude till now is a lot of large Siberian taimen. Here   are authentic data on capture fishes in weight of 70, 80 kgs! And more than 30 kgs  weight fishes are catch in annually. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Trophies:</b> except taimen   to fishers are interesting lenoks,   Amur grayling, sig-hadary and the Amur pike.  Since August, 15th  a Siberian salmon (salmons through passage). \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Terms:</b> since June, 10th по10 October. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Group:</b> 6 persons.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Residing conditions:</b> the alloy on boats, a camp. With itself it is necessary to take personal things packed in hermetic bags, tackles, sleeping bags. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Duration of fishing:</b> at will of fishermen. Recommended duration of fishing of 7 days.\r\n</p>\r\n1st day: Arrival in Khabarovsk airport. Trip from Khabarovsk to  Briakan (the bus 15  hours - 680 km) Probably helicopter   Khabarovsk -Uda- Khabarovsk . An additional touch of 10 hours. \r\n<br/>\r\n2nd day: In the presence of flight weather a start on the river (helicopter MI-8, 2 hour), fishing. \r\n<br/>\r\n3rd -  8th day: an alloy, fishing. \r\n<br/>\r\n9th day: the helicopter  To Briakan , a car to Khabarovsk, settlement in a hotel. \r\n<br/>\r\n10th day:   start from Khabarovsk airport.\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Cost of a package Khabarovsk Habarovsk:</b> from one fisherman …………  (at group not less than 6 persons).\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Into cost enters:</b> a meeting, a seeing-off, transport expenses to a place of fishing and back, the guide, the cook, a food, the equipment and equipment, the licenses.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n<b>Into cost does not enter:</b> hotel accommodation, payment of additional luggage, insurance, spirits, a satellite communication, other services which have been not provided by the preliminary arrangement.\r\n</p>\r\n',31,1),(5,'Pacific salmons tour. Kamchatka rivers','Kamchatka ','2010-03-07 12:00:00','2013-12-22 20:53:03','<p align=\'center\'><h2 class=\'fishing_tour_name\'>Kamchatka programs.</h2></p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThis is the edge of Russia, extended from the north to the south mountainous peninsula.  Extremely productive sea of Okhotsk supply Kamchatka from the West, from the East - Pacific ocean. On both coasts of Kamchatka there are lots of great rivers, big and small. Lowlands, marshy tundra and the most different reservoirs. These are extremely interesting places and first of all to appreciate a fishing component of travel. Total amount of the rivers with salmon is more than 1100! Fishing on each river of Kamchatka will always have the features, every small river is  unique. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe amount of the rivers on the east coast much less than on the west part. The largest river of  Kamchatka peninsula named  Kamchatka river. Very extended waterway with several settlements on coast.  The river Kamchatka is one of the main fish rivers. From the point of view of sports fishing it does not represent anything especial, but its inflows (too the large rivers) represent huge interest. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe rivers of the western extremity of Kamchatka are interesting to that the considerable quantity of a salmon here comes. First of all: king salmon, red salmon, cherry salmon, chum, pink salmon. In August comes hords of coho – silver salmon, and in September some rivers of Kamchatka receiving the queen of Kamchatka -- steelhead  salmon. During of all season you can fish rainbow trout, numerous amounts of char and arctic grayling. The biggest river of the western coast is the river Big.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<b><u>Kamchatka Climat Month Temperatures</u></b>\r\n</p>\r\nJanuary - 04/-10C (24/14) <br/>\r\nFebruary - 05/-11C (23/12F) <br/>\r\nMarch - 02/-10C (28/14F) <br/>\r\nApril - 05 / + 01C (23/33F) <br/>\r\nMay + 02 / + 08C (35/46F) <br/>\r\nJune + 06 / + 15C (42/59F) <br/>\r\nJuly + 10 / + 20C (50/68F) <br/>\r\nAugust + 12 / + 20C (53/68F) <br/>\r\nSeptember + 08 / + 15C (46/59F) <br/>\r\nOctober +07/-0C (44/32F) <br/>\r\nNovember - 04/-0C (24/32F) <br/>\r\nDecember - 04/-09C (24/16F) <br/>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\'fishing_river_title\'>How to get here.</h3>\r\n\r\nYour destination  is Yelizovo Airport,  Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky.<br/>\r\nInformation about flights, airlines and prices you will find on the following sites: <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nTimetable of the Yelizovo Airport: <a href=\'http://www.airagency.ru/English/index.htm\'>http://www.airagency.ru/English/index.htm</a><br/>\r\n“Transaero” airline: <a href=\'http://www.transaero.ru/en/index.html\'>http://www.transaero.ru/en/index.html</a><br/>\r\n“Vladavia” airline: <a href=\'http://www.vladavia.ru/en/passengers/\'>http://www.vladavia.ru/en/passengers/</a><br/>\r\n“Rossiya Airlines”: <a href=\'http://www.pulkovo.ru/en/\'>http://www.pulkovo.ru/en/</a><br/>\r\n“Aeroflot” company: <a href=\'http://www.aeroflot.ru/eng/\'>http://www.aeroflot.ru/eng/</a>\r\n<br/><br/>',14,1),(6,'Salmon fishing in Russia. Salmon and big trout tour. North Kola peninsula ','North Kola \r\npeninsula fishing','2010-05-08 05:38:27','2012-02-13 13:51:30','<p align=\'center\'><h2 class=\'fishing_tour_name\'>North Kola peninsula fishing.</h2></p>\r\n<h3 class=\'fishing_river_title\'>Trout rounds</h3>\r\n<h4>\r\n\r\nSalmon and Trout fishing in Russia.\r\nThe stationary camp - Upper Varzina<br/>\r\nThe stationary camp - Drozdovka<br/>\r\nThe stationary cam - Sidorovka</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4 class=\'fishing_chapter_header\'>The short description of the rounds.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nNorthern coast Kola peninsula, a stationary camp. <br/>\r\nA way of catching is flyfishing only. A principle of fishing is C&R. <br/>\r\nDaily rotation of pools (it agree the made schedule). <br/>\r\nA trophy: the Atlantic salmon, the Lake trout/brown trout, a sea trout, a humpback salmon, char, whitefish.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe beginning of a season – June.<br/>\r\nThe end of a season – August. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nDuration of round - 7 days / 7 nights.<br/>\r\nCapacity of camp - 6 rods.<br/>\r\nPlacing three-local (heated tents with a timber floor).<br/>\r\nA food - thrice (a hot breakfast and a supper + a lunch on fishing).\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 class=\'fishing_chapter_header\'>The short description of a camp.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nResiding heated tents (18 sq.) with a timber floor, three beds (folding bed) and small bedside tables. Table tent (18 sq.) with the big table, folding armchairs and a small bar.<br/>\r\nThe personal camp-manager, the head cook, the senior guide and the worker on camp.<br/>\r\nThere is a marching bath and an electricity.  \r\n</p>\r\n<h4 class=\'fishing_chapter_header\'>The short description of a round.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSaturday<br/>\r\nThe beginning of round. A meeting in Murmansk airport. A transfer Murmansk –  Lovozero  (a minibus - time in a way 3 hours). A transfer of Lovozero – camp Drozdovka (the helicopter - time in a way of 50 minutes). Arrival in a camp. A supper.</br>\r\n<br/><br/>\r\nSunday-Friday<br/>\r\nFishing on the river.<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nSaturday<br/>\r\nThe termination of round, a breakfast. A transfer from  a camp to Lovozero (the helicopter - time in a way of 50 minutes). A transfer Lovozero - Murmansk, (a minibus - time in a way 3 hours). A start from Murmansk airport.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 class=\'fishing_chapter_header\'>Cost of a round.</h4>\r\nAsk for additional info, please.\r\n\r\n<h5>In cost it is included:</h5>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAdmission registration on the right of stay in a border zone.<br/>\r\nA meeting - a seeing-off in airport of Murmansk.<br/>\r\nResiding on 3 persons in tent.<br/>\r\nThree meals a day (a hot breakfast and a supper + a lunch on fishing).<br/>\r\nConsultations of the senior guide.<br/>\r\nLicenses for fishing.<br/>\r\nA transfer from Murmansk  to Murmansk.<br/>\r\nAttention: the luggage weight should not exceed 20 kg.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Into cost does not enter:</h5>\r\n\r\nHotel accommodation (in case of non-flying weather).<br/>\r\nSpirits and low alcohol drinks.<br/>\r\nSatellite communication payment to suit the own ends.<br/>\r\nInsurance.<br/>\r\nAir flight to Murmansk.<br/>\r\n<br/>',NULL,1),(7,'Arctic charr tour. Greenland','Greenland','2010-05-09 18:19:27','2012-12-11 07:55:30','<p align=\'center\'><h2 class=\'fishing_tour_name\'> Arctic char fishing program in Greenland.</h2></p>\r\n<h3 class=\'fishing_river_title\'> Three camps – three rivers fly-out program. </h3>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThis is our gem of all Greenlandic fishing adventures we can offer. It combines camping experiences, Sisimiut hospitality, extreme mobility and the opportunity to fish three different prime waters of Western Greenland. During the 6 full fishing days’ program clients will spend six nights in riverside tent camps and three nights in lodging on rotational basis. Group capacity for this particular program should be 4. Group will switch the rivers round after each two days fishing session. In between fly-outs the whole group will gather up in Sisimiut to share impressions, have some fine meals and drinks and, of course – take a shower.\r\n</p>\r\n<h4 class=\'fishing_chapter_header\'>Typical itinerary:</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nDay I. 09:10 – 11:15 flight Copenhagen-Kangerlussuaq-Sisimiut; transfer to the helicopter landing site; flight to the first river (app. 1/3  hrs); half day’s fishing session; accommodation in tent camp equipped with twin personal tents; overnight.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nDay II. full fishing day in location 1; overnight in tent camp.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nDay III. half day’s fishing session; app. at the noon the group will be picked up and transferred to Sisimiut  to spend the night. Accommodation in a hotel Seaman’s House; three course dinner at a restaurant Lady and Vagabond. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nDay IV. morning fly out to the second river (app. ¼ hrs); full fishing day; accommodation in tent camp equipped with twin personal tents; overnight.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nDay V. full fishing day in location 2; overnight in tent camp.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nDay VI.  morning fishing; app. at the noon the group will be picked up and transferred to Sisimiut  to spend the night. Accommodation in a hotel Seaman’s House; three course dinner at a restaurant Lady and Vagabond. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nDay VII. morning fly out to the third river (app. ¼ - 1/3 hrs); full fishing day; accommodation in tent camp equipped with twin personal tents; overnight.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nDay VIII. full fishing day in location 3; overnight in tent camp.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nDay IX. morning fishing; app. at the noon the group will be picked up and transferred to Sisimiut  to spend the night. Accommodation in a hotel Seaman’s House; three course dinner at a restaurant Lady and Vagabond. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nDay X. morning transfer to the Sisimiut airport; 11:15 – 21:10 flight Sisimiut-Kangerlussuaq-Copenhagen. \r\n</p>\r\n<h4 class=\'fishing_chapter_header\'>Cost of a round.</h4>\r\nAsk for additional info, please: chavangafishing@gmail.com\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Price includes:</b> three RT helicopter flights; 6 days of fishing; guiding services; accommodation in tent camps (6 nights in personal twin tent); full board during stay in tent camps (fishermen are expected helping prepare meals); accommodation in Sisimiut (3 nights with three course dinner and breakfast); fishing license.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Price does not include:</b> RT flight Copenhagen-Sisimiut; additional meals while staying in Sisimiut; gratuities to personnel; alcoholic beverages; insurance; visa fees.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Weeks available:</b> July 24-august 02; July 28-august 06; July 30-august 08.\r\n</p>\r\n<h3 class=\'fishing_river_title\'>One camp- one river fly- out program.</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nGroup capacity for this   program should be 4 (helicopter transfer) or 5 (motorboat).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe 6 full fishing days’ program.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Price includes:</b> three RT helicopter flights; 6 days of fishing; guiding services; accommodation in tent camps (6 nights in personal twin tent); full board during stay in tent camps (fishermen are expected helping prepare meals); accommodation in Sisimiut (3 nights with three course dinner and breakfast); fishing license.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Price does not include:</b> RT flight Copenhagen-Sisimiut; additional meals while staying in Sisimiut; gratuities to personnel; alcoholic beverages; insurance; visa fees.\r\n</p>\r\n',NULL,1),(9,'Salmon fishing in Russia.  Strelna River tour. ','Salmon fishing in Russia.  Strelna River tour. ','2011-09-20 22:09:37','2013-12-22 20:53:13','<h2 class=\'fishing_tour_name\'>The River Strelna Tour</h2>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>The river description.</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n\r\nSalmon fishing in Russia.\r\nThis river is located in 50 km to the east from Chavanga river. Strelna is considered as the large river, it\r\nis the fifth biggest river on Kola Peninsula. Certainly, the size of the river from the point of view of the\r\nfisherman, depends on season. The spring high water in the beginning of May, carries a large amount of\r\nwater, but and in the middle of summer during dry time, it is a little water, and the river is accessible on\r\nall sites.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe lower part of the river, close to the seaside is wide and spacious, with the very accessible banks.\r\nFirst half of mile from the seaside, the river flows through rock and mountains. Here are the set of\r\npicturesque rocks and falls. River banks are firm, rocky, covered with large stones and pebble. Water\r\ncarries hardly a brownish, \"tea\" shade. But in a dry season water almost colourless. Futher up the\r\nriver, after all the falls and rocks, the valley extends and the river becomes quieter, stone rifts and fast\r\ncurrent streams changing each other.\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Fishes</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe Atlantic salmon and sea trout regularly comes into the river. These are the kinds of fish, fishermen coming here for. Plenty of graylings and a local brown trout who reaches the large sizes and quite interesting to catch for the fishermen.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nPopulation of a salmon in Strelna reaches the considerable sizes. The river is quite far from the closest local village so there is a minimal chance of poaching. As well as on other rivers running into the White sea, the fresh income of salmon becomes pretty usual thing. The biggest amount of fresh salmon is taken place in the autumn, September and the beginning of October and Spring in the end of May and first half of June. But there is also a summer course of a salmon, sometimes intensive enough. The largest fishes enter the river in the spring and from the end of August when it is possible to catch copies more than 10 kg in weight. But fish is in the river all season and at any time it is possible to catch a salmon. The prime- time for salmon is considered from 15th of May till 15th Of June. At this time the fish waits downstream from waterfalls. Therefore it is very convenient to fish directly near camp, within the lower part of the river. This time also estimated more expensive. The second peak of salmon fishing comes in September. From first weeks of September, autumn fish, which differs special physical standards, begin to come to the river.</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nSeparate interest is represented by fishing the sea trout. The sea trout here is a the typical sea form of silver colouring and the local form which differs brown colouring and large black stains. During the best time when high water falls down, trout of 2-3 kg come across, large fishes to 4-4.5 kg in weight are considered. The end of June - July are considered as the best time for fishing the large trout. In August the size of a trout begins to decrease, but at this time, fresh salmon comes to the river increasing the population of sea trout. By the end of August, and in September fishing the trout goes on recession. Therefore as the best time for hunting for a large trout consider the end of June - July.</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThus, it is possible to combine fishing the salmon and a trout or to choose purely trout variant in the middle of summer.</p>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Camp</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe camp Strelna is located in a picturesque place on Island in delta decks at the sea. Distance to the coast is around 300 metres, to the river - less than 100 metres. The camp consists of 4 wooden houses, in each of them 3 rooms for clients, shower, toilet, a room for drying and the furnace are located. Each room accommodate 2 fishermen. Houses are equipped by electric heating of water. The dining room is located in a separate structure, the lunch hall is equipped with fireplace, bar with alcoholic drinks, TV and others. Nearby, there is a kitchen. The spacious bath with a sweating room is constructed here, on river bank. </p>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>The fishing organisation</p>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Terms</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe fishing season opens since May, 15th. The season end legally is not limited, depending on weather conditions it is possible to finish a season in the middle of October.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Capacity</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe camp contains up to 10 fishermen. The standard group at the beginning of the season is 10 persons. In the middle of a season, groups usually consists of 8 persons. Groups with smaller quantity of participants are accepted after the coordination of details with the organizer of tour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Duration of tour</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nStandard tour is consider as  6 + days  of fishing. Recommended day of arrival and departure is Saturday. \r\nUnder individual demands duration of tour can be prolonged or reduced.</p>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Transfer</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe camp is in 50 km to the east from Chavanga river. Approximately the distance from Varzuga mouth makes about 90 km. From Umba river, the distance is around 230 km.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nTo get to the Strelna camp is possible by the helicopter, by the truck or the powerboat by the sea.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe approximate plan of  transfer looks so:\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\nThe Variant. Meeting at the airport of Murmansk. Delivery by a minibus to Umba takes  5 hours. Road to the mouth of Varzuga takes 3.5 hours by the off-road car. Then 3 hours to the river Chavanga and then  2.5 hours to Strelna. It  is considerate as  inexpensive and a reliable variant.</li>\r\n<br/>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\nThe Variant. Meeting at the airport of Murmansk. Delivery by a minibus to Umba takes  5 hours. Road to the mouth of Varzuga takes 3.5 hours by the off-road car. Then by the powerboat to Strelna takes 1.5 - 2 hours. It is an inexpensive and convenient variant. This method of trasportation depends on weather conditions on the sea.\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\nThe Variant. Meeting at the airport of Murmansk. Delivery by a minibus to Umba takes 5 hours. Than from Umba there is  1 hour flight by helicopter straight to Strelna camp. It is comfortable enough and fast way of delivery. A bit more expensive way of traveling.</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\nThe Variant is a mix of helicopter  (way to or back way ) and  off-road car. Meeting at the airport of Murmansk. Delivery by a minibus to Umba takes 5 hours. Than from Umba there is  1 hour flight by helicopter straight to Strelna camp. Back way we start by  the off-road car,  minibus from Umba to Murmansk.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>The tour includes:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\nResiding at camp of 7 nights</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\nЗ-х a single food</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\nCost of fishing licences</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\nUsing a camp infrastructure - dryers, a bath, a chimney hall, the TV</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\nServices of the cook and the guide</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>\r\n6 days of fishing</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Tour doesn’t include:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>Transfer from Murmansk to camp and back</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>Alcohol</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>Insurance</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>The Visa help</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3 class=\'fishing_river_title\'>Mixed Programs</h3>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\n We offer you the mixed programs including fishing on the river Chavanga and on the river Strelna.\r\nIt allows you:\r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>Visiting 2 rivers, which have different character, conditions and fishing behavior, in one program tour.</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>Allows to break a transfer from Murmansk into 2 parts, that makes the time spend during transfer more enjoyable.</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>It is possible to prolong duration of tour from 6-7 nights to 9 or 10 nights, which is difficult to make on a one river tour.</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>It is possible to make tour individual, choosing the river with the best conditions for the period of tour.</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>It is possible to choose the most convenient time and a way of a transfer for movement between camps of Chavanga and Strelna. It is possible to begin with fishing  on Chavange, then to visit Strelna or on the contrary that reduces time of a continuous transfer.</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>Choosing the mixed program, it is easier to organise non-standard groups.</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>It is possible to make the program answering to financial inquiries of clients.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe mixed programs usually include some days of fishing on the river Chavanga and some days on Strelna. Usually, these programs are popular in the middle of a season when they become more accessible at the price. Their basic advantage is possibility to correct the program on a place, having prolonged or having reduced fishing terms on Chavange or on Strelna. Here it is possible to consider an individual condition of the river directly during tour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Cost of standard tour on the river Strelna.</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nCost is defined by cost of standard tour calculated for 8 persons and cost of additional services, mainly - a transfer from a place of an arrival to base. \r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>Salmon tour.<br/>\r\nThe best time for fishing the salmon is from 15.05 till 15.06 and in the autumn from 10.09 till 15.10  is …….. Euros from the person plus transfer cost. That is the cost of standard tour for standard group of 8 persons makes ………….. Euros plus cost of a transfer for all group.</li>\r\n<li style=\'text-align:justify;\'>The Mixed salmon and trout programs in the middle of a season is low - …… Euros from the client plus transfer cost.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nGroups with quantity of clients less than 8 persons pay extra the missing amount to cost of standard tour.</p>\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Cost of the mixed programs</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nCost of the mixed programs is calculated at cost of actual days of fishing on the rivers Chavanga and Strelna. The price depends on the program of tour and is co-ordinated with the organizer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\'font-weight:bold\'>Booking and payment conditions</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nPlaces and tour time are considered reserved for as clients after the coordination of all details with the organizer and a guarantee of payment of tour.</p>\r\n<p class=\'fishing_main_text\'>\r\nThe down payment makes 30 % from a total cost of tour and is brought by cash or on the bill of the organizer not later than 01.03 current years. The overall cost is paid to the organizer on a place, on arrival to a catching place.</p>',74,1),(10,'Kola Peninsula salmon tour','','2013-12-22 20:54:32','2013-12-22 20:54:32','',NULL,0),(11,'Pacific salmon and trout tour','','2013-12-22 21:01:36','2013-12-22 21:01:36','',NULL,0),(12,'Giant hucho-taimen tour','','2013-12-22 21:02:21','2013-12-22 21:02:21','',NULL,0);
