INSERT INTO `post_comments` VALUES (1,'Chavanga','Yes, it`s possible. But we are fishing in our own camp in the lowest part of the river. If you want to use official camps, please contact with Silver of Ponoj or another organization. Usually we get to the river by big motorboat from Chavanga. It`s less expensive than helicopter flights from Murmansk. If you need more info- please ask me.',80,'2010-11-06 12:46:59','2010-11-06 12:46:59'),(2,'Chavanga','Erwan Hi! Yes, Srimph is a fantastic agressive fly for trouts that are living in top parts of rivers and in lakes. It work as provocative lure. If trout is agressive too or you can provoke fish to attack - it may be an effective fly (beginning of a season, June or prespawn perion). But in a situation of natural feeding or selctive feeding we must to find another fly - insect imitation or fry. The best all year flies are nymphs!!! You need only to use correct presentation. Thanks!',77,'2010-11-06 12:52:42','2010-11-06 12:52:42'),(3,'Chavanga','Daniel Hi! OK, I hope I will have a good news for you. Thanks',24,'2010-11-06 12:52:58','2010-11-06 12:52:58'),(4,'Chavanga','Bastian Hi! You know in early season we need large bright flies like Ally`s shrimp or Cascade, much red and orange colors. In summer- smaller sizes and more black like in Green But and Red But. From another side you can use all assortment of salmon and trouts-grayling flies to fish salmon successfully only need to find right method of presentation.',21,'2010-11-06 12:53:23','2010-11-06 12:53:23'),(5,'Chavanga','Yes, you have Program 2 and 3. If you wish we may combine an individual program Chavanga+another river, Indiora or Pialitsa for example, to get an exellent variant ( salmon and special trout fishing). Very interesting variant is to use mix Program 1 - our Lodge (salmon fishing) and Top Camp (salmon + special grayling fishing during 1-2-3 days, as you want). By this way we can get a mix programs to achieve the most interesting variants in depending of season and river conditions and your wishes.',18,'2010-11-06 12:53:49','2010-11-06 12:53:49'),(6,'Chavanga','Tomas, hi! Early season first part of June- weighted bright flies like as Shrimp, Cascade on double hooks # 4-6. \r\nGood luck, Vasyl',7,'2010-11-06 12:54:17','2010-11-06 12:54:17'),(7,'Chavanga','Yes, it`s possible to use smaller MI- 2 helico for 2-3-4 rods trip. One flight hour costs 1500$.',9,'2010-11-06 12:54:33','2010-11-06 12:54:33'),(8,'Chavanga','В этом году уже вряд ли. На 2011 на 5 июня были свободны 3 места. Это лучшее время и конец сентября, конечно.',11,'2010-11-06 12:54:48','2010-11-06 12:54:48'),(9,'Chavanga','Alex Hi! About prices and all detailes, please, ask me chavangafishing.@gmail.com \r\nAnd I think that the best time to fish trophy trouts is the end of June. Another best period is the beginning of summer, early June, but this time is not so comfortable to fish.',13,'2010-11-06 12:55:08','2010-11-06 12:55:08'),(10,'Chavanga','Alex, sorry! Not the end of June but the end of August, before spawn time.',13,'2010-11-06 12:55:19','2010-11-06 12:55:19'),(11,'Chavanga','David, we just have 3 free places in a tour from 14.09 till 22.09.2010. 7 days fishing in a village lodge (program 1). The middle of september is a beginning of new autumn run of salmon and usually is a interesting time to fish resident and fresh salmon. Plus trouts and graylings.',16,'2010-11-06 12:55:41','2010-11-06 12:55:41'),(12,'Chavanga','Ok, please send me e-mail  chavangafishing@gmail.com, I will give you additional info, maps, description and prices. Thanks.',82,'2010-11-07 08:29:07','2010-11-07 08:29:07'),(13,'Chavanga','Tomas, hi! You may have 2 rods, strong one   #8 10`00`` for hight water level, big heavy flies, long casts. Another one for pleasure fishing #7 in summer low water condition and different   techniques.\r\nFriendly, Vasil',84,'2010-11-20 20:07:50','2010-11-20 20:07:50'),(14,'Chavanga','Hi Jean! This year is a year of pink salmon, You must help us to get best way, flies and TECHNIQUE  to fish pinks!',90,'2011-04-22 19:58:42','2011-04-22 19:58:42'),(18,'Chavanga',' \r\n\r\nDear  Ianus!   Pinks run started at 05.07 but the main run started at 15-17.07 after some cold days and rain. Water temperature fall down from 22 to 16 and fish became very active. Some info about humpback - pinks you may see in my article on  \r\n\r\n   http://blog.chavanga.com/search/label/humpback%20salmon \r\n\r\nAll the best!',104,'2011-07-20 18:17:32','2011-07-20 18:17:32'),(19,'Chavanga',' River situation changes very quickly. June beginning was difficult, but July was very good. The biggest problem was very hot weather and water temperature during first part of June. \r\n I think that you can use all flies ( there is no reason to think about one or two the best flies) - only we need to use floating lines and delicate presentation in spots and pockets, single hand rods are more usefull now to change presentation according to water level and river spots. Tippets - very important in clear and low water - 0.26-0.28 not a 0.35. But in night time - 0.35 is not a problem. Every good river hole has some fishes, we need to fish correctly only.',104,'2011-07-25 09:08:49','2011-07-25 09:08:49'),(20,'Chavanga','Hi Jacky!\r\nYes, its very interesting thing -  salmon q-ty, so i will prepare most important info  and public it  here or in Blog. Cheers!',123,'2011-12-02 09:35:26','2011-12-02 09:35:26'),(21,'Chavanga','Dear Tony! Thanks for contacting us using email: \r\n\r\n        chavangafishing@mail.mail',125,'2012-01-09 11:02:31','2012-01-09 11:02:31'),(22,'Chavanga','На здоровье. Если есть какие-нибудь вопросы, пожалуйста, задавайте. Здесь минимум коммерчески подправленной информации и о некоторых вещах можно говорить начистоту.  ',130,'2012-02-06 18:52:31','2012-02-06 18:52:31'),(24,'Chavanga',' Hello, Lenox! Now there is a free week from 05 to 12.7, from 16 to 22.7 and from 14 to 21.09. This is the best time for such programs. It is possible to use the second half of July and August. This is also a good time for fishing and sea trout and salmon',134,'2012-04-24 06:58:24','2012-04-24 06:58:24'),(25,'Chavanga','Yes, its possible. Usually we fish   C&R licences, so we use   double- or - single barbless hook spin lures. The fishing organization is the same as for fly fishers, no problems. Welcome!',143,'2013-02-19 08:11:50','2013-02-19 08:11:50'),(26,'Chavanga','Welcome, Piere!\r\nGood luck and biggest salmon in 2013!',141,'2013-02-19 09:09:32','2013-02-19 09:09:32'),(27,'Chavanga','HI Peter!\r\nThis time-intensive silver salmon  run  to the   river from the sea. Therefore, fishing is fun. Weather - end of September, approximately equal to our European mid November. There is no snow and temperatures above zero.',148,'2014-01-28 08:42:05','2014-01-28 08:42:05'),(30,'Chavanga','I am pleased that these short notes interest you.\r\nAll the best!',188,'2014-11-21 14:22:05','2014-11-21 14:22:05');
